{"id": 3564, "title": "Ticket #3564: Rename MEMORY_LIMIT parameter to CGROUP_MEMORY_LIMIT_POLICY", "description": "<blockquote>\nIn our documentation, we reserved all params that end in _LIMIT to be used for concurrency limits.  The relatively new cgroup based parameter \"MEMORY_LIMIT\" collides with this.  Before the stable series comes out, we should rename this to be CGROUP_MEMORY_LIMIT_POLICY.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2013-Apr-05 15:20:02 by eje:</em> <br/>\n\nI wonder if we should adopt the prefix convention for cc-limits, as in:\n\n<p>CONCURRENCY_LIMIT_&lt;name&gt;</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-08 08:56</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1f2ec148f707479545989a8132991033a248a09d\">[35344]</a></span>: Fixup param table for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3564\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('3564'); return false;\" title=\"Rename MEMORY_LIMIT parameter to CGROUP_MEMORY_LIMIT_POLICY\">#3564</a></span>  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-05 13:03</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c1fea464a3506110b50209289ebecaf5a9dc0976\">[35342]</a></span>: fix a typo and add version history item for knob name change, MEMORY_LIMIT becomes CGROUP_MEMORY_LIMIT_POLICY ===GT=== <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=3564\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_w